A 16-year-old boy has died and another teenager was seriously injured after their car crashed into a tree.
The one-vehicle collision happened on the A966 between Dysart and Coaltown of Wemyss in Fife at about 12.50am today.
The passenger, Brian Phimister, died at the scene while the 18-year-old man driving the car was taken to hospital.
 

A Police Scotland spokesman said: &quot;A BMW 3 Series car left the road before colliding with a tree resulting in serious injury to the 18-year-old male driver and his 16-year-old male passenger.
&quot;The driver has been taken to the Victoria Hospital in Kirkcaldy for treatment, however, the passenger was pronounced dead at the scene.
&quot;Inquiries into the full circumstances surrounding this incident are ongoing and anyone who can assist road policing officers with their investigation is asked to contact police immediately.&quot;

